@scenario_hash:600a36ceff9d7405
Scenario: bc-implementer template names a decomposition/right-sizing discipline on the existing "break down into sub-issues" activity with guidance or a "guidance pending" marker
  Given the §4.2 BC-shop activity "break down into sub-issues" already exists in the authoritative activity catalogue
  When I read the bc-implementer template via "shop-templates show bc-implementer"
  Then the content names a decomposition or right-sizing discipline attached to the existing breakdown activity rather than introducing breakdown as a new activity
  And the content states that the discipline develops the quality of an existing §4.2 activity, so its criteria live in the role template and are iterable without spec churn
  And the discipline has a contiguous block — a subsection or a line that names it — that contains at minimum one sentence of guidance OR an explicit marker of the form "guidance pending" (case-insensitive)
  And the decomposition discipline does not appear as a bare list item with neither guidance nor a "guidance pending" marker
